HEADWORD: Tentation
<hw>Ten*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tentatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>tentation</ets>. See
<er>Temptation</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Trial; temptation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A mode of adjusting or operating
by repeated trials or experiments.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tentative</ent>⟦br⟧
